# Plaid / Tech Spend hold

Do **not** commit, push, merge, or include Plaid / Tech Spend changes in production releases unless Bryan **explicitly** asks to ship Plaid (e.g. "push Plaid" or "deploy Tech Spend").

## When Bryan says "push" / "push all changes" / "push today's work"

- Exclude any Plaid-related work from the commit/push.
- If uncommitted Plaid files exist, leave them unstaged (or stash locally) and only push the rest.
- Do not re-add Tech Spend nav (`mspend`), `MemberTechSpendView`, `/api/portal/plaid/*`, `/api/plaid/*`, `src/lib/plaid/*`, `plaid` / `react-plaid-link` packages, or `0073_plaid_tech_spend` migration.

## Allowed without explicit ask

- Local experimentation is fine — restoring the Tech Spend tab / Plaid files for local development is expected.
- Still do **not** commit or push that work until he says to ship Plaid specifically.
- When mixing with other work: leave Plaid/Tech Spend paths unstaged (or stash them) so non-Plaid commits/pushes stay clean.
